column1: % The MSBN-S Station is located on the southern end of Masonboro Island
column2: NC. The station is a 10' tower with its meteorological sensor positioned approximately 8.4 feet above the primary sand dune. The station samples continuously at 1 Hz and averages the data every 6 minutes. Data is transmitted every 30 minutes. The installation and maintenance of the station is funded
column4: by grants from the National Science Foundation and U.S. Coastal Research Program. This site/dataset was established on 07/01/2021. Please be cautious in the vicinity of the station and do not climb on the tower or guy wires.
